Russian Equity Movers: Polymetal, Rosneft, Bank of Moscow

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-07-27T16:22:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/russian-equity-movers-polymetal-and-severstal-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slipped 0.9
percent to 1,706.28 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index retreated 0.6 percent to 1,976.18.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), the Russian gold and silver miner,
advanced for a third day as gold surged to an all-time high and
silver increased. Its shares jumped 1.8 percent to 586.9 rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX),  Russia â€™s largest oil producer sank
by its most in more than a week, losing 1.7 percent to 237.53
rubles. Crude oil for September delivery fell $2.01, or 2
percent, to $97.58 a barrel in  New York  after a U.S. government
report showed an unexpected increase in inventories.  Bank of Moscow (MMBM RX) advanced for the second day after
RIA Novosti reported shareholder Vitaly Yusufov signed a
preliminary agreement to sell his 19.9 percent stake to VTB
Group. The stock rose 0.4 percent to 805.9 rubles. The deal ends
uncertainty over whether VTB will gain a 75 percent stake, said
Marco Casas, a New York-based vice-president for equity sales at
